@startuml ai-controllers-advisors-sequence
title Chat controllers &amp; advisors — sequence diagram

actor Client
participant "ImageController" as ImageCtrl
participant "MemoryChatController" as MemCtrl
participant "MultiModelChatController" as MultiCtrl
participant "OllamaChatController" as OllamaCtrl
participant "TimeController" as TimeCtrl
participant "ChatClient" as ChatClient
participant "TokenLoggerAdvisor" as TokenLogger
participant "TimeTools" as Tools
participant "ImageModel" as ImageModel
participant "Model\n(Ollama / OpenAI)" as Model

== Image generation ==
Client -> ImageCtrl: GET /api/image?message=...
ImageCtrl -> ImageModel: call(new ImagePrompt(message))
ImageModel --> ImageCtrl: imageResponse
ImageCtrl --> Client: base64 image JSON

== Memory-scoped chat ==
Client -> MemCtrl: GET /api/chat-memory?message=...\n(username header)
MemCtrl -> ChatClient: prompt().advisors(CONVERSATION_ID)\n.user(message).call()
ChatClient -> TokenLogger: adviseCall(request, chain)
TokenLogger -> Model: nextCall(request)\n(memory advisor injects prior turns first)
Model --> TokenLogger: response + usage
TokenLogger -> TokenLogger: log token usage
TokenLogger --> ChatClient: response
ChatClient --> MemCtrl: content()
MemCtrl --> Client: 200 OK

== Multi-model chat (e.g. /api/openai/chat) ==
Client -> MultiCtrl: GET /api/openai/chat?message=...
MultiCtrl -> ChatClient: prompt(message).call()
ChatClient -> TokenLogger: adviseCall(request, chain)
TokenLogger -> Model: nextCall(request)
Model --> TokenLogger: response + usage
TokenLogger -> TokenLogger: log token usage
TokenLogger --> ChatClient: response
ChatClient --> MultiCtrl: content()
MultiCtrl --> Client: response text
note right of MultiCtrl
  Same shape for /ollama/chat, /email,
  /prompt-stuffing, /stream, and the
  structured-output endpoints
  (chat-bean, chat-list, chat-map, chat-bean-list).
end note

== Plain Ollama chat with inline system prompt ==
Client -> OllamaCtrl: GET /api/chat?message=...
OllamaCtrl -> ChatClient: prompt().system("IT helpdesk assistant...")\n.user(message).call()
ChatClient -> TokenLogger: adviseCall(request, chain)
TokenLogger -> Model: nextCall(request)
Model --> TokenLogger: response + usage
TokenLogger -> TokenLogger: log token usage
TokenLogger --> ChatClient: response
ChatClient --> OllamaCtrl: content()
OllamaCtrl --> Client: response text

== Time-tool chat ==
Client -> TimeCtrl: GET /api/tools/local-time?message=...\n(username header)
TimeCtrl -> ChatClient: prompt().advisors(CONVERSATION_ID)\n.user(message).call()
ChatClient -> TokenLogger: adviseCall(request, chain)
TokenLogger -> Model: nextCall(request)\n(defaultTools = TimeTools)
Model -> Tools: getCurrentLocalTime() / getCurrentTime(timeZone)\n(model decides to call a tool)
Tools --> Model: current time string
Model --> TokenLogger: final answer + usage
TokenLogger -> TokenLogger: log token usage
TokenLogger --> ChatClient: response
ChatClient --> TimeCtrl: content()
TimeCtrl --> Client: 200 OK

== Application startup — RagAdvisor bean assembly (not per-request) ==
participant "ChatClientConfig" as Config
participant "RagAdvisor" as RagAdv
participant "ChatClientFactory" as Factory
Config -> RagAdv: retrievalAugmentationAdvisor(vectorStore, chatClientFactory)
RagAdv -> Factory: createOllama()\n(for the query-translation chat client)
Factory --> RagAdv: ChatClient.Builder
RagAdv --> Config: RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor bean
note right of RagAdv
  Runs once at startup, not on the request
  path of any of the five controllers above.
  The resulting bean is only injected into
  ragMemoryChatClient (used by RagController).
end note

@enduml
